{
  "texts": [
    "3.3.The general idea of the SP+CSP protocol is to partition the N = 2 n basis states into M = 2 m non-overlapping sets of size N M. Computational basis states for which the first m bits agree (when written in binary) are placed into the same set.",
    "Denote the M sets by J i with i = 0,..., M -1.",
    "For each i, we let y i = j∈Ji |x j | 2.",
    "We first prepare the state of m qubits (m < n):U SP |0 m ⟩ = |ϕ⟩ = 1 ∥y∥ 2 m -1 i=0 y i |i⟩(5)The total state is now |ϕ⟩ ⊗ |0 n-m ⟩.Next, we perform the controlled state preparation operation U CSP, defined byU CSP (|i⟩ ⊗ |0 n-m ⟩) = y -1 i j∈Ji x j |j⟩(6)for a particular |i⟩ state being controlled on, so thatU CSP (|ϕ⟩ ⊗ |0 n-m ⟩) = |ψ⟩ = 1 ∥x∥ 2 n -1 j=0 x j |j⟩ (7)The circuit diagram is shown in Fig. 6.",
    "Implementation details of U SP and U CSP are shown in Fig. 7 and Fig."
  ]
}